Now I have a thorough understanding of the entire codebase. Let me compile the detailed implementation plan.

---

## Rocket Mode (Pilot POV) -- Detailed Implementation Plan

This plan covers five new files and modifications to two existing files. The implementation follows the existing patterns observed throughout the Universe module: ref-based animation loops with `batchDraw()`, single `<Shape>` sceneFunc for batch canvas drawing, glass morphism CSS for HTML overlays, and hooks that return refs/callbacks consumed by layers.

---

### 1. New File: `client/src/components/Universe/hooks/useRocketMode.js`

**Purpose**: All simulation state lives in refs. A single rAF loop runs the physics. No React re-renders per frame.

**Constants** (top of file):

```js
const MIN_Z = 0.5;         // Star passes behind camera; recycle
const MAX_Z = 800;          // Far spawn depth
const SPAWN_Z_RANGE = 400;  // Random range when recycling: MAX_Z - SPAWN_Z_RANGE to MAX_Z
const MAX_SPEED = 12;       // Units/frame at full throttle
const ACCEL = 0.25;         // Per-frame acceleration
const BRAKE = 0.15;         // Per-frame deceleration
const TURN_RATE = 0.035;    // Radians per frame
const FRICTION = 0.985;     // Passive velocity decay
const SORT_INTERVAL = 5;    // Re-sort stars every N frames
const TARGET_Z_MIN = 2;     // Minimum z for targeting consideration
const TARGET_DIST_MAX = 150; // Max projected screen-distance for targeting bracket
const STRETCH_FACTOR = 2.5;  // Max scaleX multiplier at max speed
const FADE_FACTOR = 0.6;     // Max opacity reduction at max speed
const SPEED_LINE_COUNT = 30;  // Number of radial speed lines
const SPEED_LINE_THRESHOLD = 0.4; // speedRatio above which speed lines appear
```

**Data structures (all refs)**:

```js
// Rocket state
const rocketPos = useRef({ x: 0, y: 0 });  // 2D world position
const heading = useRef(0);                   // Radians, 0 = right, PI/2 = down
const velocity = useRef(0);

// Stars array (mutable, never triggers React render)
// Each entry: { postId, worldX, worldY, z, color, colorRgb, radius, title, authorName, likeCount }
const starsRef = useRef([]);

// Sorted indices for draw order (far first)
const sortedIndicesRef = useRef([]);

// Key state
const keysRef = useRef({ w: false, s: false, a: false, d: false });

// Targeted star index (closest to screen center with z > TARGET_Z_MIN)
const targetIndexRef = useRef(-1);

// Frame counter for sort interval
const frameRef = useRef(0);

// rAF handle
const rafRef = useRef(null);

// Layer ref for batchDraw
const layerRef = useRef(null);

// Screen center (updated on resize)
const screenCenter = useRef({ x: window.innerWidth / 2, y: window.innerHeight / 2 });

// Active flag
const activeRef = useRef(false);
```

**Initialization function** `enter(galaxyPosts, galaxyCenter, stageSize)`:

```js
// Called when user clicks "Explore Galaxy"
// galaxyPosts: array of post objects belonging to this galaxy
// galaxyCenter: { x, y } world position of galaxy
// stageSize: { width, height }

rocketPos.current = { x: galaxyCenter.x, y: galaxyCenter.y };
heading.current = -Math.PI / 2; // pointing "up"
velocity.current = 0;
screenCenter.current = { x: stageSize.width / 2, y: stageSize.height / 2 };

// Build star array with random z distribution
const rng = mulberry32(Date.now());
starsRef.current = galaxyPosts.map(post => {
    const uid = post.users?.id ?? post.user_id;
    const color = getStarColor(uid);
    const rgb = parseHex(color);
    const likeCount = post.like_count ?? (post.likes?.[0]?.count ?? 0);
    return {
        postId: post.id,
        worldX: post.universe_x ?? post.display_x,
        worldY: post.universe_y ?? post.display_y,
        z: MIN_Z + rng() * (MAX_Z - MIN_Z),
        color,
        colorRgb: rgb,
        radius: getStarRadius(likeCount),
        title: post.title || '',
        authorName: post.users?.name ?? post.user_name ?? 'Anonymous',
        likeCount,
        post,  // keep reference for navigation
    };
});

// Initial sort
rebuildSortedIndices();
activeRef.current = true;
startLoop();
```

**rAF loop** `tick()`:

```js
const tick = () => {
    if (!activeRef.current) return;

    const keys = keysRef.current;
    const dt = 1; // fixed timestep (frame-based)

    // 1. Heading update (A/D)
    if (keys.a) heading.current -= TURN_RATE;
    if (keys.d) heading.current += TURN_RATE;

    // 2. Velocity update (W/S)
    if (keys.w) velocity.current = Math.min(velocity.current + ACCEL, MAX_SPEED);
    else if (keys.s) velocity.current = Math.max(velocity.current - BRAKE, -MAX_SPEED * 0.3);
    else velocity.current *= FRICTION;

    // Clamp near-zero
    if (Math.abs(velocity.current) < 0.01) velocity.current = 0;

    // 3. Update rocket world position
    const h = heading.current;
    const v = velocity.current;
    rocketPos.current.x += Math.cos(h) * v;
    rocketPos.current.y += Math.sin(h) * v;

    // 4. Update star z values (simulate forward motion)
    const stars = starsRef.current;
    for (let i = 0; i < stars.length; i++) {
        stars[i].z -= v * 0.5; // z decreases as we move forward

        // Recycle stars that pass behind camera
        if (stars[i].z < MIN_Z) {
            stars[i].z = MAX_Z - Math.random() * SPAWN_Z_RANGE;
            // Scatter around current rocket position
            stars[i].worldX = rocketPos.current.x + (Math.random() - 0.5) * 2000;
            stars[i].worldY = rocketPos.current.y + (Math.random() - 0.5) * 2000;
        }
        // Also recycle if too far behind
        if (stars[i].z > MAX_Z + 100) {
            stars[i].z = MIN_Z + Math.random() * 20;
        }
    }

    // 5. Sort every SORT_INTERVAL frames
    frameRef.current++;
    if (frameRef.current % SORT_INTERVAL === 0) {
        rebuildSortedIndices();
    }

    // 6. Find targeted star
    updateTarget();

    // 7. Trigger canvas redraw
    if (layerRef.current) {
        layerRef.current.batchDraw();
    }

    rafRef.current = requestAnimationFrame(tick);
};
```

**Projection helper** (consumed by RocketLayer's sceneFunc):

```js
const project = (star, cx, cy) => {
    const relX = star.worldX - rocketPos.current.x;
    const relY = star.worldY - rocketPos.current.y;

    // Rotate by negative heading so "forward" is screen-up
    const cosH = Math.cos(-heading.current + Math.PI / 2);
    const sinH = Math.sin(-heading.current + Math.PI / 2);
    const rotX = relX * cosH - relY * sinH;
    const rotY = relX * sinH + relY * cosH;

    const projX = cx + rotX / star.z;
    const projY = cy + rotY / star.z;
    const scale = 1 / star.z;

    return { projX, projY, scale };
};
```

**Target update**:

```js
const updateTarget = () => {
    const cx = screenCenter.current.x;
    const cy = screenCenter.current.y;
    const stars = starsRef.current;
    let bestIdx = -1;
    let bestDist = TARGET_DIST_MAX;

    for (let i = 0; i < stars.length; i++) {
        if (stars[i].z < TARGET_Z_MIN || stars[i].z > MAX_Z * 0.8) continue;
        const { projX, projY } = project(stars[i], cx, cy);
        const dx = projX - cx;
        const dy = projY - cy;
        const d = Math.sqrt(dx * dx + dy * dy);
        if (d < bestDist) {
            bestDist = d;
            bestIdx = i;
        }
    }
    targetIndexRef.current = bestIdx;
};
```

**Key handlers** (registered/unregistered on enter/exit):

```js
const handleKeyDown = (e) => {
    const key = e.key.toLowerCase();
    if (key === 'w' || key === 'arrowup') keysRef.current.w = true;
    if (key === 's' || key === 'arrowdown') keysRef.current.s = true;
    if (key === 'a' || key === 'arrowleft') keysRef.current.a = true;
    if (key === 'd' || key === 'arrowright') keysRef.current.d = true;
};

const handleKeyUp = (e) => {
    const key = e.key.toLowerCase();
    if (key === 'w' || key === 'arrowup') keysRef.current.w = false;
    if (key === 's' || key === 'arrowdown') keysRef.current.s = false;
    if (key === 'a' || key === 'arrowleft') keysRef.current.a = false;
    if (key === 'd' || key === 'arrowright') keysRef.current.d = false;
};
```

**Return value**:

```js
return {
    enter,           // (galaxyPosts, galaxyCenter, stageSize) => void
    exit,            // () => void -- stops loop, cleans up key listeners
    layerRef,        // ref for RocketLayer to attach to Konva Layer
    starsRef,        // ref to mutable star array
    sortedIndicesRef,// ref to sorted indices
    rocketPos,       // ref to {x,y}
    heading,         // ref to heading angle
    velocity,        // ref to velocity
    targetIndexRef,  // ref to targeted star index
    screenCenter,    // ref to screen center
    project,         // projection function
    isActive: activeRef, // ref, boolean
    getTargetedPost, // () => post object or null
    getSpeedRatio,   // () => number 0..1
    MAX_SPEED,       // constant, exposed for HUD
};
```

---

### 2. New File: `client/src/components/Universe/layers/RocketLayer.jsx`

**Purpose**: Single Konva `<Layer>` with a single `<Shape>` using `sceneFunc` for batch canvas rendering. No individual Konva node components.

**Pattern reference**: Follows the exact pattern from `WormholeLayer.jsx` (lines 226-241) and `DeepSpaceLayer.jsx` (lines 24-37) -- a single `<Shape>` with `sceneFunc`, `perfectDrawEnabled={false}`, `listening={false}`.

```jsx
import React from 'react';
import { Layer, Shape } from 'react-konva';

const TWO_PI = Math.PI * 2;

const RocketLayer = React.memo(({ rocketMode }) => {
    const {
        layerRef, starsRef, sortedIndicesRef, rocketPos,
        heading, velocity, targetIndexRef, screenCenter,
        project, getSpeedRatio, MAX_SPEED,
    } = rocketMode;

    return (
        <Layer ref={layerRef} listening={false}>
            <Shape
                sceneFunc={(ctx) => {
                    const stars = starsRef.current;
                    const sorted = sortedIndicesRef.current;
                    const cx = screenCenter.current.x;
                    const cy = screenCenter.current.y;
                    const speedRatio = Math.abs(velocity.current) / MAX_SPEED;
                    const targetIdx = targetIndexRef.current;

                    // -- Speed lines (behind stars) --
                    if (speedRatio > 0.4) {
                        const lineAlpha = (speedRatio - 0.4) / 0.6; // 0..1
                        ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(180,210,255,${lineAlpha * 0.3})`;
                        ctx.lineWidth = 1;
                        for (let i = 0; i < 30; i++) {
                            const angle = (i / 30) * TWO_PI;
                            const innerR = 50 + speedRatio * 80;
                            const outerR = innerR + speedRatio * 300;
                            ctx.beginPath();
                            ctx.moveTo(
                                cx + Math.cos(angle) * innerR,
                                cy + Math.sin(angle) * innerR
                            );
                            ctx.lineTo(
                                cx + Math.cos(angle) * outerR,
                                cy + Math.sin(angle) * outerR
                            );
                            ctx.stroke();
                        }
                    }

                    // -- Stars: painter's algorithm (far first) --
                    for (let si = 0; si < sorted.length; si++) {
                        const idx = sorted[si];
                        const star = stars[idx];
                        if (!star) continue;

                        const { projX, projY, scale } = project(star, cx, cy);

                        // Viewport culling
                        if (projX < -200 || projX > cx * 2 + 200 ||
                            projY < -200 || projY > cy * 2 + 200) continue;

                        const baseR = star.radius * scale * 40; // amplify for visibility
                        if (baseR < 0.3) continue; // too small

                        // Hyper-jump distortion
                        const stretchX = 1 + speedRatio * 2.5;
                        const opacity = Math.max(0.1, 1 - speedRatio * 0.6);

                        const { r, g, b } = star.colorRgb;
                        const drawR = Math.min(baseR, 30); // cap radius

                        ctx.save();
                        ctx.translate(projX, projY);
                        ctx.scale(stretchX, 1); // horizontal stretch

                        // Outer glow
                        const glowR = drawR * 3;
                        const glow = ctx.createRadialGradient(0, 0, 0, 0, 0, glowR);
                        glow.addColorStop(0, `rgba(${r},${g},${b},${0.5 * opacity})`);
                        glow.addColorStop(0.4, `rgba(${r},${g},${b},${0.15 * opacity})`);
                        glow.addColorStop(1, `rgba(${r},${g},${b},0)`);
                        ctx.beginPath();
                        ctx.arc(0, 0, glowR, 0, TWO_PI);
                        ctx.fillStyle = glow;
                        ctx.fill();

                        // Core
                        ctx.beginPath();
                        ctx.arc(0, 0, drawR * 0.4, 0, TWO_PI);
                        ctx.fillStyle = `rgba(255,255,255,${0.9 * opacity})`;
                        ctx.fill();

                        ctx.restore();

                        // Targeting bracket (not stretched)
                        if (idx === targetIdx) {
                            const bracketSize = Math.max(drawR * stretchX * 4, 18);
                            const half = bracketSize / 2;
                            const corner = bracketSize * 0.3;
                            const time = performance.now();
                            const pulse = 0.6 + 0.4 * Math.sin(time * 0.004);

                            ctx.strokeStyle = `rgba(100,220,255,${pulse})`;
                            ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
                            ctx.setLineDash([4, 3]);

                            // Top-left corner
                            ctx.beginPath();
                            ctx.moveTo(projX - half, projY - half + corner);
                            ctx.lineTo(projX - half, projY - half);
                            ctx.lineTo(projX - half + corner, projY - half);
                            ctx.stroke();

                            // Top-right corner
                            ctx.beginPath();
                            ctx.moveTo(projX + half - corner, projY - half);
                            ctx.lineTo(projX + half, projY - half);
                            ctx.lineTo(projX + half, projY - half + corner);
                            ctx.stroke();

                            // Bottom-left corner
                            ctx.beginPath();
                            ctx.moveTo(projX - half, projY + half - corner);
                            ctx.lineTo(projX - half, projY + half);
                            ctx.lineTo(projX - half + corner, projY + half);
                            ctx.stroke();

                            // Bottom-right corner
                            ctx.beginPath();
                            ctx.moveTo(projX + half - corner, projY + half);
                            ctx.lineTo(projX + half, projY + half);
                            ctx.lineTo(projX + half, projY + half - corner);
                            ctx.stroke();

                            ctx.setLineDash([]);
                        }
                    }
                }}
                perfectDrawEnabled={false}
                listening={false}
            />
        </Layer>
    );
});

RocketLayer.displayName = 'RocketLayer';

export default RocketLayer;
```

---

### 3. New File: `client/src/components/Universe/components/RocketHUD.jsx`

**Purpose**: Pure HTML overlay (not Konva). Reads from the hook's refs via a low-frequency `useState` updater (10 Hz, not 60fps) to display HUD information.

```jsx
import React, { useEffect, useState, useCallback } from 'react';
import styles from '../Universe.module.css';

const HUD_UPDATE_MS = 100; // 10 Hz for HUD text updates

const RocketHUD = ({ rocketMode, onExit, onInteract }) => {
    const [hudState, setHudState] = useState({
        speed: 0,
        speedRatio: 0,
        targetName: null,
        targetAuthor: null,
    });

    useEffect(() => {
        const interval = setInterval(() => {
            const speedRatio = rocketMode.getSpeedRatio();
            const target = rocketMode.getTargetedPost();
            setHudState({
                speed: Math.abs(rocketMode.velocity.current).toFixed(1),
                speedRatio,
                targetName: target?.title || null,
                targetAuthor: target?.users?.name ?? target?.user_name ?? null,
            });
        }, HUD_UPDATE_MS);

        return () => clearInterval(interval);
    }, [rocketMode]);

    // Enter/Space to interact with targeted star
    useEffect(() => {
        const handleKey = (e) => {
            if (e.key === 'Enter' || e.key === ' ') {
                e.preventDefault();
                onInteract();
            }
            if (e.key === 'Escape') {
                onExit();
            }
        };
        window.addEventListener('keydown', handleKey);
        return () => window.removeEventListener('keydown', handleKey);
    }, [onInteract, onExit]);

    const barWidth = `${Math.min(hudState.speedRatio * 100, 100)}%`;

    return (
        <div className={styles.rocketHud}>
            {/* Speed indicator */}
            <div className={styles.rocketSpeedBar}>
                <div className={styles.rocketSpeedLabel}>SPEED</div>
                <div className={styles.rocketSpeedTrack}>
                    <div
                        className={styles.rocketSpeedFill}
                        style={{ width: barWidth }}
                    />
                </div>
                <div className={styles.rocketSpeedValue}>{hudState.speed}</div>
            </div>

            {/* Targeted star info */}
            {hudState.targetName && (
                <div className={styles.rocketTarget}>
                    <div className={styles.rocketTargetName}>{hudState.targetName}</div>
                    {hudState.targetAuthor && (
                        <div className={styles.rocketTargetAuthor}>by {hudState.targetAuthor}</div>
                    )}
                    <div className={styles.rocketTargetPrompt}>Press ENTER to read</div>
                </div>
            )}

            {/* Controls hint */}
            <div className={styles.rocketControls}>
                <span>W/S Throttle</span>
                <span>A/D Turn</span>
                <span>ENTER Read</span>
                <span>ESC Exit</span>
            </div>

            {/* Exit button */}
            <button className={styles.rocketExitBtn} onClick={onExit}>
                Exit Rocket Mode
            </button>
        </div>
    );
};

export default RocketHUD;
```

