### 1. New File: `client/src/components/Universe/hooks/useRocketMode.js`

**Purpose**: All simulation state lives in refs. A single rAF loop runs the physics. No React re-renders per frame.

**Constants** (top of file):

```js
const MIN_Z = 0.5;         // Star passes behind camera; recycle
const MAX_Z = 800;          // Far spawn depth
const SPAWN_Z_RANGE = 400;  // Random range when recycling: MAX_Z - SPAWN_Z_RANGE to MAX_Z
const MAX_SPEED = 12;       // Units/frame at full throttle
const ACCEL = 0.25;         // Per-frame acceleration
const BRAKE = 0.15;         // Per-frame deceleration
const TURN_RATE = 0.035;    // Radians per frame
const FRICTION = 0.985;     // Passive velocity decay
const SORT_INTERVAL = 5;    // Re-sort stars every N frames
const TARGET_Z_MIN = 2;     // Minimum z for targeting consideration
const TARGET_DIST_MAX = 150; // Max projected screen-distance for targeting bracket
const STRETCH_FACTOR = 2.5;  // Max scaleX multiplier at max speed
const FADE_FACTOR = 0.6;     // Max opacity reduction at max speed
const SPEED_LINE_COUNT = 30;  // Number of radial speed lines
const SPEED_LINE_THRESHOLD = 0.4; // speedRatio above which speed lines appear
```

**Data structures (all refs)**:

```js
// Rocket state
const rocketPos = useRef({ x: 0, y: 0 });  // 2D world position
const heading = useRef(0);                   // Radians, 0 = right, PI/2 = down
const velocity = useRef(0);

// Stars array (mutable, never triggers React render)
// Each entry: { postId, worldX, worldY, z, color, colorRgb, radius, title, authorName, likeCount }
const starsRef = useRef([]);

// Sorted indices for draw order (far first)
const sortedIndicesRef = useRef([]);

// Key state
const keysRef = useRef({ w: false, s: false, a: false, d: false });

// Targeted star index (closest to screen center with z > TARGET_Z_MIN)
const targetIndexRef = useRef(-1);

// Frame counter for sort interval
const frameRef = useRef(0);

// rAF handle
const rafRef = useRef(null);

// Layer ref for batchDraw
const layerRef = useRef(null);

// Screen center (updated on resize)
const screenCenter = useRef({ x: window.innerWidth / 2, y: window.innerHeight / 2 });

// Active flag
const activeRef = useRef(false);
```

**Initialization function** `enter(galaxyPosts, galaxyCenter, stageSize)`:

```js
